<subSubSection id="C334EFADFFB9632673130697FDD94652" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B91BC26FFB9632673130697FEBF43D2" blockId="46.[264,647,924,985]" box="[264,346,959,985]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<figureCitation id="1315A0A3FFB9632673130697FEBF43D2" box="[264,346,959,985]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–42" captionStartId="44.[264,383,1740,1764]" captionTargetBox="[268,1321,320,1715]" captionTargetId="figure-44@44.[267,1326,319,1725]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURES 32–42. Melaloncha spp., female, ovipositor, left lateral (except Fig. 40, bottom). Figures. 39 and 40 showing intersegmental membrane and sclerite of intersegment 7–8." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5070726" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5070726/files/figure.png" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B91BC26FFB9632673130126FBF0445A" blockId="46.[264,1322,1038,1825]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis id="B95A6034FFB9632673130126FE414423" bold="true" box="[264,420,1038,1064]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Recognition.</emphasis>
This yellow species recognized by the shape of the ovipositor, which is rounded laterally, and apically narrowed to a broad, rounded point.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B91BC26FFB9632673230176FDD94652" blockId="46.[264,1322,1038,1825]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis id="B95A6034FFB9632673230176FE354473" bold="true" box="[312,464,1118,1144]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Description.</emphasis>
Female (male unknown). Body length 2.0 mm. Frons dark yellow, bare of setulae; ocellar triangle with dark color connecting ocelli. Frons 0.46 head width. Medial furrow absent. Ocular setae brown dorsally, yellow laterally and ventrally; genal setae yellow. Flagellomere 1, aristomeres 1–2 and base of 3 yellow; most of aristomere 3 brown. Palpus white; palpal setae brown. Scutum yellowish­brown, with small posterolateral dark brown spot. Scutellum yellow, with anterolateral dark round spot. Pleuron yellowish­brown except basalare black. Legs yellowish­brown. Combined length of foretarsomeres equal to length of foretibia. Foretarsal claws recurved, with large basal lobe. 
<collectingRegion id="49EA72C4FFB96326734800B7FE7045B2" box="[339,405,1439,1465]" country="New Zealand" name="West Coast" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Costa</collectingRegion>
0.51 wing length. Halter yellow. Abdominal tergites anteriorly yellow, posteriorly black; tergites 2–5 with black color extending farther forward medially. Venter of abdomen yellow. Ovipositor basally yellow, mostly black; rounded, expanded slightly at midlength; apex broadly rounded in dorsal view; with long, curved setae throughout, but especially dense ventrally.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
